fields.description:
When running euca-delete-group against an invalid group, it returns a non-AWS compatible error.

{code}
# euca-delete-group appscale1
DeleteSecurityGroupType: Failed to find security group: appscale1 for arn:aws:euare::345590850920:
{code}

In AWS, the following error is presented:

{code}
$ ec2-delete-group appscale-test2
Client.InvalidGroup.NotFound: The security group 'appscale-test2' does not exist
{code}

*Suggested Fix*

Per AWS EC2 Error codes, we should return the following error:

InvalidGroup.NotFound	 Specified group name does not exist.

* Reference *
* http://docs.amazonwebservices.com/AWSEC2/latest/APIReference/api-error-codes.html
fields.summary: euca-delete-group against an invalid group doesn't provide AWS compatible error
fields.environment:
*HA*

* 2 x CLC/Walrus
* 2 x CC
* 1 x SC
* 3 x NCs
